nett AL. Environmental erectile dysfunction: Can the environment really be hazardous to your erectile health? Journal of Andrology. 2008 May 6;29(3):229-36 <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18187396">https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18187396</a> (accessed November 1, 2019.) Written comments provided to Human Rights Watch by Mark Robson, Board of Governors Distinguished Service Professor at Rutgers University’s School of Environmental and Biological Sciences, April 29, 2019.</p>
